PN,39703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F397A1776773466
OL,3,CManchester leg of Tour de France
OL,4,CFemmes 2027 revealed
OL,6,FThey will then tackle the Cote de
OL,7,FDelph (2.1km at 6.3%), circling down
OL,8,Fthrough Rochdale before entering
OL,9,FManchester City Centre and passing
OL,10,FManchester Cathedral.
OL,12,FThe riders will line up for the stage
OL,13,Ffinish on Deansgate, ending stage one
OL,14,Fof the race on 30 July.
OL,16,FCyclists will then leave Manchester
OL,17,Ffor the Peak District in stage two a
OL,18,Fday later.
